{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idc3ac7f99-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3728"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3728"},"text":"§ 3728.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Exemption from State anti-usury provisions","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"If, under any law of the United States, loans and mortgages insured under title I or title II of the National Housing Act are exempt from the application of the provisions of any State constitution or law (1) limiting the rate or amount of interest, discount points, or other charges which may be charged, taken, received, or reserved by lenders, (2) restricting the manner of calculating such interest (including prohibition of the charging of interest on interest), or (3) requiring a minimum amortization of principal, then loans guaranteed or insured under this chapter are also exempt from the application of such provisions.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idc3ac7f9a-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87"},"text":"(Added ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/128/tIV/s401/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 96–128, title IV, § 401(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1979-11-28"},"text":"Nov. 28, 1979","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/93/986"},"text":"93 Stat. 986","children":[],"tail":", § 1828; amended "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/66/tV/s501/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 97–66, title V, § 501(b)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1981-10-17"},"text":"Oct. 17, 1981","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/95/1032"},"text":"95 Stat. 1032","children":[],"tail":"; renumbered § 3728, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/102/83/s5/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 102–83, § 5(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1991-08-06"},"text":"Aug. 6, 1991","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/105/406"},"text":"105 Stat. 406","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idc3ac7f9b-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idc3ac7f9c-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"idc3ac7f9d-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The National Housing Act, referred to in text, is ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1934-06-27/ch847"},"text":"act June 27, 1934, ch. 847","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/48/1246"},"text":"48 Stat. 1246","children":[],"tail":". Titles I and II of the Act are classified generally to subchapters I (§ 1702 et seq.) and II (§ 1707 et seq.), respectively, of chapter 13 of Title 12, Banks and Banking. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t12/s1701"},"text":"section 1701 of Title 12","children":[],"tail":" and Tables."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"idc3ac7f9e-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1991—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/102/83"},"text":"Pub. L. 102–83","children":[],"tail":" renumbered "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t38/s1828"},"text":"section 1828 of this title","children":[],"tail":" as this section."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","